r Ingelheim Fonds: PhD Fellowships\n\n',5,NULL,'Doctoral sponsorships to ambitious doctoral project in the field of basic biomedical research at an internationally leading laboratory over a period of about 3 years. Fellows receive personal mentoring, participate in seminars on the presentation and discussion of research projects and attend communication trainings designed to especially respond to the needs of scientists. For non-European scientists wishing to do research in Europe','2 years to 3 years','monthly grant of EUR 1,550 +  other allowances ','under the age of 27, admission to a doctoral programme, project proposal\n\n','1 February, 1 June and 1 October of each year','https://www.daad.de/deutschland/stipendium/datenbank/en/21148-scholarship-database/?status=&origin=192&subjectGrps=&daad=&q=&page=7&detail=10000164','http://www.bifonds.de/fellowships-grants/phd-fellowships/application.html','','دانشجویان مهندسی پزشکی قبول شده در دوره دکتری می توانند برای این بورس اقدام کنند تا 3 سال از دوره دکتری خود را در آلمان بگذرانند. شرایط پروژه های مورد قبول در لینک دوم آمده است. تاییدیه استاد راهنمای ایران روی پروژه لازم است. سن متقاضی باید زیر 27 سال باشد. ','',1),(372,'2017-03-05 11:08:16','2017-03-05 11:08:16','Bayer Science & Education Foundation: Otto Bayer Scholarships\n\n',6,NULL,'The scholarships are aimed at students and young professionals in the following disciplines: biology and molecular biology, biotechnology and bioinformatics, chemistry and biochemistry, pharmacy and computational life sciences. The Otto Bayer scholarship finances international students and young professionals with up to two years of experience who wish to study, research or do an internship in Germany. ','two to 12 months','€ 75,000 , varies depending on the project','two years of experience in the fields mentioned ','Application duration: June 1 and July 18, 2017','https://www.daad.de/deutschland/stipendium/datenbank/en/21148-scholarship-database/?status=&origin=192&subjectGrps=&daad=