ternational standards and printed in journals and/or by publishing houses.\nSupport of the German host institution, evidenced by a detailed expert\\\'s report from the academic host as well as the host\\\'s agreement and the confirmation from the administration at the host institution.\nTwo supporting expert reviews from academics (at the applicant\\\'s own institute or other institutes, where possible including some outside the applicant\\\'s country of origin).\nLanguage skills: scholars in the humanities or social sciences and physicians must have a good knowledge of German if it is necessary to carry out the project successfully; otherwise a good knowledge of English; scientists and engineers must have a good knowledge of German or English.\nNo previous Sofja Kovalevskaja Award.\nOrigin: Foreign academics staying in Germany are eligible to apply if they have lived outside Germany for a minimum of 12 months in total in the 18-month period prior to the application submission deadline. Educational residents are subject to the regulations governing Germans. German academics are eligible to apply if they have been working in an academic capacity abroad for a longer time. For more details please check with the FAQ.\nThe Humboldt Foundation assumes that candidates will abide by the Rules of Good Scientific Practice and the legally-binding principles of scientific ethics during the application and sponsorship periods.','the next application round is scheduled to start in Spring 2017 \nDeadline will be July of 2017 ','https://www.humboldt-foundation.de/web/kovalevskaja-award.html','','','برنامه ای جهت افرادی که حداکثر سال است دکتری گرفته اند. باید در سطح پژوهشگر حرفه با با قابلیت شبکه سازی و راهبری تیم باشند. این حمایت سالانه برای طرح به مجموع 1.65 میلیون یورو (هر نفر نهایتا 275 هزار یورو) در مدت 5 سال. (اشاره نشده که هر سال این میزان پرداخت میشود یا نهایت این میزان و طرح نهایتا تا 5 سال؟). حتما استاد باید سرآمد باشد و انتشارات بین المللی زیادی داشته باشد.  ','',6),(411,'2017-03-05 11:10:02','2017-03-05 11:10:02','International Climate Protection Fellowship for young climate experts from developing countries',6,NULL,'\nSubmit an application, if you\n• are a future leader from a non-European transition or developing country \n• are active in any of the following areas: scientific, engineering-based, legal, economic, health-related or social aspects of climate change\n• are interested in spending a year working with a host of your choice in Germany on a research-based project you have developed yourself in the field of climate protection and climate-related resource conservation\n','1 year','between €2,150 and €2,650,','First university degree (Bachelor’s or equivalent), completed less than 12 years previously, counting back from the end of the application period (1 March 2017);\nLeadership skills demonstrated by initial experience in leadership positions and/or appropriate references;\nExtensive work experience (at least 48 months at the time of application) or a successfully completed doctorate in the field of climate protection or climate-related resource conservation;\nScientific publications (for post-doctoral applicants) in peer-reviewed journals according to international standards;\nA detailed statement by a host in Germany, including a mentoring agreement; details of the proposal must be discussed with the prospective host prior to application;\nCitizenship of a non-European transition or developing country (see list of countries) which is also the applicant’s habitual residence and place of work;\nVery good knowledge of English and/or German, documented by appropriate language certificates;\nTwo expert references by individuals qualified to comment on the candidate’s professional, personal and, if applicable, academic eligibility as well as his/her leadership potential.','42795','https://www.humboldt-foundation.de/web/icf.html','','','افرادی که حتما در زمینه آب و هو ا و تغییرات آن و منابع آن تحقیقات داشته اند. حدود 20 حمایت هر سال انجام میشود. به جهت این که انتخاب از کشورهای محدودی است، احتمال پذیرش کمی بالاتر میرود. انتخاب توسط استاد آلمانی شروع میشود.','',6),(412,'2017-03-05 11:10:02','2017-03-05 11:10:02','Humboldt Research Fellowship for Postdoctoral Researchers\n',6,NULL,'Submit an application if you are a researcher from abroad with above average qualifications, at the beginning of your academic career and only completed your doctorate in the last four years. A Humboldt Research Fellowship for postdoctoral researchers allows you to carry out long-term research (6-24 months) in Germany. Applicants choose their own topic of research and their academic host.\nScientists and scholars of all nationalities and disciplines may apply to the Alexander von Humboldt Foundation online at any time. The Humboldt Foundation grants approximately 500 Humboldt Research Fellowships for postdoctoral researchers and experienced researchers annually. Short-term study visits, participation in congresses and training courses cannot be financed.','6-24 months)',' 2,650 EUR per month','Doctorate or comparable academic degree (Ph.D., C.Sc. or equivalent), completed less than four years prior to the date of application. Candidates who have nearly completed their doctoral degrees are eligible to apply provided that they submit the manuscript of their dissertation or publications containing the results of their dissertation.\nAcademic publications reviewed according to international standards and printed in journals and/or by publishing houses.\nConfirmation that research facilities are available and mentoring agreement and a detailed expert\\\'s report by an academic host at a research institution in Germany. Details of the research outline including information on the intended duration of the fellowship must be agreed with the intended host before applying.\nExpert reviews from the doctoral supervisor and one other academic qualified to give well-founded comments on the applicant\\\'s eligibility, preferably including a reviewer not working at the applicant\\\'s own institute.\nLanguage skills: scholars in the humanities or social sciences and physicians must have a good knowledge of German if it is necessary to carry out the research successfully; otherwise a good knowledge of English; scientists and engineers must have a good knowledge of German or English.\nApplications to continue a research stay already underway can only be considered in exceptional cases. The applicant may not have spent an extended period in Germany prior to application. Potential applicants who have been in Germany for more than six months at the time of application are not eligible to apply.','no deadline','https://www.humboldt-foundation.de/web/humboldt-fellowship-postdoc.html','','','نهایتا 4 سال از زمان اخذ مدرک گذشته باشد. حدود 500 حمایت مایل در سال. میزان 2650 یورو در ماه برای مدت6-24 ماه کار تحقیقاتی، رزومه قوی میخواهد و این که حتما قبلا آلمان دوره طولانی اقامت نداشته باشند. انتخاب توسط استاد آلمانی شروع میشود.','',6),(413,'2017-03-05 11:10:03','2017-03-05 11:10:03','Humboldt Research Fellowship for Experienced Researchers',6,NULL,'Submit an application if you are a researcher from abroad with above average qualifications, completed your doctorate less than twelve years ago, already have your own research profile and are working at least at the level of Assistant Professor or Junior Research Group Leader or have a record of several years of independent academic work. A Humboldt Research Fellowship for experienced researchers allows you to carry out long-term research (6-18 months) in Germany. Applicants choose their own topic of research and their academic host. The fellowship is flexible and can be divided up into as many as three stays within three years.','6-18 months','3,150 EUR per month','Doctorate or comparable academic degree (Ph.D., C.Sc. or equivalent), completed less than twelve years prior to the date of application. If it is not possible or customary to take a doctorate in the candidate\\\'s subject or country, applications may be submitted up to twelve years after commencing publication activity;\nThe candidate\\\'s own research profile documented by a comprehensive list of academic publications reviewed according to international standards and printed in journals and/or by publishing houses;\nConfirmation that research facilities are available and mentoring agreement and a detailed expert\\\'s report by an academic host at a research institution in Germany; details of the research outline including information on the intended duration of the fellowship must be agreed with the intended host before applying;\nTwo expert reviews from important collaborative partners and/or academics from the candidate\\\'s own institute and, if possible, from abroad;\nLanguage skills: scholars in the humanities or social sciences and physicians must have a good knowledge of German if it is necessary to carry out the research successfully; otherwise a good knowledge of English; scientists and engineers must have a good knowledge of German or English;\nApplications to continue a research stay already underway can only be considered in exceptional cases. The applicant may not have spent an extended period in Germany prior to application. Potential applicants who have been in Germany for more than six months at the time of application are not eligible to apply;','no deadline','https://www.humboldt-foundation.de/web/humboldt-fellowship-experienced.html','','','نهایتا 12 سال از زمان اخذ مدرک گذشته باشد. حدود 500 حمایت مالی در سال. میزان 3150 یورو در ماه برای مدت 6-18 ماه کار تحقیقاتی، رزومه قوی میخواهد و این که حتما قبلا آلمان دوره طولانی اقامت نداشته باشند. انتخاب توسط استاد آلمانی شروع میشود.','',6),(414,'2017-03-05 11:10:03','2017-03-05 11:10:03','Humboldt Research Award\n',5,NULL,'The award is granted in recognition of a researcher\\\'s entire achievements to date to academics whose fundamental discoveries, new theories, or insights have had a significant impact on their own discipline and who are expected to continue producing cutting-edge achievements in the future.\nAcademics from abroad, regardless of their discipline or nationality, may be nominated for a Humboldt Research Award. The Alexander von Humboldt Foundation particularly encourages the nomination of qualified female academics.\nAward winners are invited to spend a period of up to one year cooperating on a long-term research project with specialist colleagues at a research institution in Germany. The stay may be divided up into blocks.\nThe Humboldt Foundation grants up to 100 Humboldt Research Awards annually.\nNominations may be submitted by established academics in Germany. Nominations may also be initiated by award winners of the Humboldt Foundation working abroad, provided that the nomination is made jointly with a colleague working in Germany. Direct applications are not accepted. The award is valued at €60,000.','up to one year ','The award is valued at €60,000.','1. The nominee must be recognised internationally as an outstandingly qualified academic (e.g. awards, positive responses to publications, etc.).\n2. The nominee\\\'s future perspectives must indicate that she/he will continue to be an active, academically influential researcher in the coming years.\n3. Detailed expert opinion by an academic working at a research institution in Germany who would like to invite the nominee to spend time researching in Germany.\n4. Two expert reviews by important international and one from German collaborative partners and/or academics.\n','','https://www.humboldt-foundation.de/web/humboldt-award.html','','','این حمایت برای مدت یک سال و به میزان 60 هزار یورو است. حدود 100 نفر در هر سال واجد شرایط می‌شوند. فاقد تاریخ اقدام است و ازاین‌جهت مناسب هست. استاد اقدام کننده می‌بایست از افراد مشهور و سرشناسی باشد که بیش از 18 سال از دریافت دکتری وی نگذشته باشد. طرح ارائه‌شده باید موجب جابه‌جایی حداقلی در مرزهای دانش شود. همچنین حمایت‌های جنبی نظیر دوره‌های آموزش زبان و (هزینه سفر نهایتاً هزار یورو یک‌بار در سال) نیز در نظر گرفته ‌شده است.دعوت توسط استاد آلمانی شروع میشود.','',6),(415,'2017-03-05 11:10:03','2017-03-05 11:10:03','German Research Chair in\n\\\"Mathematics and its Applications\\\" at the\nAfrican Institute for Mathematical Sciences (AIMS) in Tanzania',3,NULL,'The call addresses highly qualified academics from all over the world who conduct application-related research in the field of mathematics, have experience in training students and (ideally) doctoral candidates.\nThe application must be supported by at least one future collaborative partner in Germany.\nThe sponsorship will initially be made available for four years and will total up to €560,000.','up to 4 years','560000','Doctorate followed by several years of research activity\nteaching experience, including proven experience in supervising students\noutstanding, internationally recognised research record\nalready have or will establish a scientific cooperation with a German institution of higher education','1 February 2017.\n','https://www.humboldt-foundation.de/web/research-chair-aims-tanzania.html','','','برای اساتیدی که در زمینه ریاضیات و آموزش عالی و پژوهشی و علی الخصوص تربیت دانشجویان دکتری سابقه دارند، این حمایت به مبلغ نهایت 560 هزار یورو در مدت 4 سال انجام میشود. نیاز هست تا با یک ظرف آلمانی مدت خوبی در زمینه آموزش عالی در  ارتباط بوده باشید و توسط آن حمایت شوید. توسط خود شما میشود  مستقیم مدارک ارسال شود. از نظر حمایت مالی بسیار عالی است. این برنامه در جهت توسعه پژوهش در حوزه ریاضیات است.','',6),(416,'2017-03-05 11:10:03','2017-03-05 11:10:03','German Research Chair in\n\\\"Mathematics and its Applications\\\" at the\nAfrican Institute for Mathematical Sciences (AIMS) in Cameroon',3,NULL,'The call addresses highly qualified academics from all over the world who conduct application-related research in the field of mathematics, have experience in training students and (ideally) doctoral candidates.\nThe application must be supported by at least one future collaborative partner in Germany.\nThe sponsorship will initially be made available for four years and will total up to €560,000.\n','up to 4 years','560000','Doctorate followed by several years of research activity\nteaching experience, including proven experience in supervising students\noutstanding, internationally recognised research record\nalready have or will establish a scientific cooperation with a German institution of higher education','1 August 2016.\n','https://www.humboldt-foundation.de/web/research-chair-aims-cameroon.html','','','برای اساتیدی که در زمینه ریاضیات و آموزش عالی و پژوهشی و علی الخصوص تربیت دانشجویان دکتری سابقه دارند، این حمایت به مبلغ نهایت 560 هزار یورو در مدت 4 سال انجام میشود. نیاز هست تا با یک ظرف آلمانی مدت خوبی در زمینه آموزش عالی در  ارتباط بوده باشید و توسط آن حمایت شوید. توسط خود شما میشود  مستقیم مدارک ارسال شود. از نظر حمایت مالی بسیار عالی است. این برنامه در جهت توسعه پژوهش در حوزه ریاضیات است.','',6),(417,'2017-03-05 11:10:03','2017-03-05 11:10:03','Georg Forster Research Fellowship',5,NULL,'• if you are a researcher with above average qualifications in a developing or transition country \n• if you intend to carry out long-term research of your own choice (6 to 24 months) at a research institution in Germany together with an academic host you have chosen yourself,\n• if your research outline includes aspects that are important for the continued development of your country or region of origin and\n• if you want to contribute to the exchange of knowledge and methods between Germany and your country of origin.\n\n',' long-term research of your own choice (6 to 24 months)',' a monthly fellowship of €2,650 for postdoctoral researchers (doctorate completed within the last four years) or €3,150 for experienced researchers (doctorate completed within the last 12 years),','• you intend to carry out long-term research of your own choice (6 to 24 months) at a research institution in Germany together with an academic host you have chosen yourself,\n• your research outline includes aspects that are important for the continued development of your country or region of origin\n\n','Not mentioned but you must assume it will take up to ten months before you receive a decision','https://www.humboldt-foundation.de/web/georg-forster-fellowship.html','','','جهت حمایت از اساتیدی که در 12 سل گذشته دکتری گرفته‌اند (حمایت 3150 یورویی در ماه) و پسا دکتری برای افرادی که کم‌تر از 4 سال گذشته دکتری گرفته‌اند (حمایت 2650 یورویی در ماه) و برای 6-24 ماه. باید طرحی توسط استاد ارائه و در آلمان توسط ایشان اجرا شود. نرخ موفقیت حدود 33% برای سال‌های قبل بوده است. دعوت توسط استاد آلمانی شروع میشود.','',6),(418,'2017-03-05 11:10:03','2017-03-05 11:10:03','Georg Forster Research Award\n',4,NULL,'\nThe Georg Forster Research Award is granted in recognition of a researcher\\\'s entire achievements to date to academics of all disciplines whose fundamental discoveries, new theories, or insights have had a significant impact on their own discipline and beyond and who are expected to continue developing research-based solutions to the specific challenges facing transition and developing countries.\nNominees must be nationals of a developing or transition country (excluding People\\\'s Republic of China and India; Furthermore, at the time of nomination, they must have had their main residence and place of work in one of these countries for at least five years.\nThe Alexander von Humboldt Foundation particularly encourages the nomination of qualified female researchers.\nThe award amount totals €60,000. In Germany, research awards are generally exempt from income tax under German tax law.\nIn addition, award winners are invited to conduct a research project of their own choosing in Germany in close collaboration with a specialist colleague. To support the collaboration, the Alexander von Humboldt Foundation may grant additional funding of up to €25,000, particularly for participating in scientific conferences, additional material resources, e.g., specialist literature and scientific equipment for the nominee’s own institute, as well as for involving junior researchers.\nAn established academic employed by a university or research institution in Germany must take the initiative to nominate a candidate for the Georg Forster Research Award. Nominations may also be initiated by award winners of the Humboldt Foundation working abroad, provided that the nomination is made jointly with a colleague working in Germany. Self-nomination is not possible.\nThe Alexander von Humboldt Foundation is granting up to six Georg Forster Research Awards annually.\n','up to 1 year, can be devided in blocks','€60.000 (+ €25.000 additional)','1. The nominee must be recognised internationally as an outstandingly qualified academic (e.g. awards, positive responses to publications, etc.).\n2. The nominee\\\'s future perspectives must indicate that she/he will continue to be an active, academically influential researcher in the coming years with relevance to the development of the nominee\\\'s own county.\n3. The nominee must be exceptionally qualified to continue developing research-based solutions to the specific challenges facing transition and developing countries.\n4. The nominee must be a national of a developing or transition country (excluding People\\\'s Republic of China and India; cf. detailed list of countries). At the time of nomination, he or she must have had his or her main residence and place of work in one of these countries for at least five years.;\n5. Detailed expert opinion (laudation) by an academic working at a research institution in Germany who would like to invite the nominee to spend time researching in Germany.\n6. Two expert reviews by important international academics and one from a German scientist/scholar;\n','42384','https://www.humboldt-foundation.de/web/georg-forster-award.html','','','اساتیدی که طرح جدید ی دارند و نیاز به توسعه طرح خود دارند. حداقل 5 سال سابقه کار در دانشگاه. این حمایت سالانه به 6 نفر اعطا می‌شود. حمایت 60 هزار یورویی و ممکن است تا 25 هزار یورو دیگر برای پوشش کنفرانس‌ها و ... پرداخت شود. انتخاب استاد باید توسط یکی از اساتید شاغل در دانشگاه/موسسه آلمان انجام شود. این طرح به‌منظور راهبری پروژه توسط گروه انتخاب‌شده توسط استاد خارجی در آلمان است..دعوت توسط استاد آلمانی شروع میشود.','',6),(419,'2017-03-05 11:10:03','2017-03-05 11:10:03','Friedrich Wilhelm Bessel Research Award\n',4,NULL,'Scientists and scholars from abroad, internationally renowned in their field, who completed their doctorates less than 18 years ago and who in future are expected to continue producing cutting-edge achievements which will have a seminal influence on their discipline beyond their immediate field of work, are eligible to be nominated for a Friedrich Wilhelm Bessel Research Award.\nAward winners are honoured for their outstanding research record and invited to spend a period of up to one year cooperating on a long-term research project with specialist colleagues at a research institution in Germany. The stay may be divided up into blocks.\nThe Humboldt Foundation grants about 20 Friedrich Wilhelm Bessel Research Awards annually.\nNominations may be submitted by established academics in Germany. Nominations may also be initiated by award winners of the Humboldt Foundation working abroad, provided that the nomination is made jointly with a colleague working in Germany. Direct applications are not accepted. The award is valued at €45,000.','up to 1 year, can be devided in blocks','45','\n1. The nominee must be recognised internationally as an outstanding researcher in his/her field (e.g. awards, positive responses to publications, etc.).\n2. Expectation that the nominee will continue to produce cutting-edge achievements which will have a seminal influence on the discipline.\n3. Doctorate completed less than 18 years ago.\n4. Detailed expert opinion by an academic working at a research institution in Germany who would like to invite the nominee to spend time researching in Germany.\nTwo expert reviews by important international and one from German collaborative partners and/or academics.\n','','https://www.humboldt-foundation.de/web/bessel-award.html','','','این حمایت برای مدت یک سال و به میزان 45 هزار یورو است. حدود 20 نفر در هر سال واجد شرایط می‌شوند. فاقد تاریخ اقدام است و ازاین‌جهت مناسب هست. استاد اقدام کننده می‌بایست از افراد مشهور و سرشناسی باشد که بیش از 18 سال از دریافت دکتری وی نگذشته باشد. طرح ارائه‌شده باید موجب جابه‌جایی حداقلی در مرزهای دانش شود. همچنین حمایت‌های جنبی نظیر دوره‌های آموزش زبان و (هزینه سفر نهایتاً هزار یورو یک‌بار در سال) نیز در نظر گرفته ‌شده است.دعوت توسط استاد آلمانی شروع میشود.','',6),(420,'2017-03-05 11:10:04','2017-03-05 11:10:04','Fraunhofer-Bessel Research Award\n',4,NULL,'Scientists and scholars from all non-European countries, who completed their doctorates less than 18 years ago, who are internationally recognised for their achievements in the field of applied research, and who in future are expected to continue producing cutting-edge achievements which will have a seminal influence on their discipline beyond their immediate field of work, are eligible to be nominated for a Fraunhofer-Bessel Research Award.\nAward winners are invited to spend a period of up to one year cooperating on a long-term research project with specialist colleagues at one of the Fraunhofer Institutes in Germany. The stay may be divided up into blocks.\nThe Humboldt Foundation and the Fraunhofer Society for the Advancement of Applied Research jointly grant up to three Fraunhofer-Bessel Research Awards annually.\nNominations may be submitted by the heads of institutes or senior academics at institutes belonging to the Fraunhofer Society. Nominations may also be initiated by award winners of the Humboldt Foundation working abroad, provided that the nomination is made jointly with a colleague working at a Fraunhofer Institute in Germany. Direct applications are not accepted. The award is valued at €45,000.\n','up to 1 year, can be devided in blocks','45','1. The nominee must be recognised internationally as an outstanding researcher in his/her field of applied research (e.g. awards, positive responses to publications, etc.).\n2. Expectation that the nominee will continue to produce cutting-edge achievementswhich will have a seminal influence on the discipline.\n3. Doctorate or comparable academic degree, completed less than 18 years prior to the date of nomination.\n4. Main place of residence/work outside Europe.\n5. Nomination by the director or senior academics at an institute belonging to the Fraunhofer Society.\n6. Detailed expert opinion by the nominators.\n7. Two expert reviews by important international and one from German collaborative partners and/or academics.\n\n\n','no dead line, each year they will have 2 Committee\n\n','https://www.humboldt-foundation.de/web/fraunhofer-bessel-award.html','','','این حمایت برای مدت یک سال و به میزان 45 هزار یورو است. حدود 20 نفر در هر سال واجد شرایط می‌شوند. فاقد تاریخ اقدام است و ازاین‌جهت مناسب هست. استاد اقدام کننده می‌بایست از افراد مشهور و سرشناسی باشد که بیش از 18 سال از دریافت دکتری وی نگذشته باشد. طرح ارائه‌شده باید موجب جابه‌جایی حداقلی در مرزهای دانش شود. همچنین حمایت‌های جنبی نظیر دوره‌های آموزش زبان و (هزینه سفر نهایتاً هزار یورو یک‌بار در سال) نیز در نظر گرفته ‌شده است.دعوت توسط استاد آلمانی شروع میشود.','',6),(421,'2017-03-05 11:10:04','2017-03-05 11:10:04','Feodor Lynen Research Fellowship',6,NULL,'Sponsorship for research stays worldwide by researchers from Germany of all disciplines and at all career stages. Applicants choose an academic host from some 15,000 academics in the Humboldt Network abroad.\n','• for post-doctoral researchers (up to four years after completing a doctorate):\n6 to 24 months\n• For experienced researchers (up to 12 years after completing a doctorate):\n6 to 18 months, divisible into a maximum of three visits over three years\n','€3,305 per month, or up to €5,320 ','1. above average academic history and academic record\n2. host\\\'s confirmation of research facilities\n3. Experienced researchers also require:\n4. their own academic profile\n5. professional experience at least at the level of assistant professor or junior research group leader or several years‘ independent scientific employment\n','At any time. A Humboldt Foundation selection committee meets in February, June and October to decide on applications. ','https://www.humboldt-foundation.de/web/lynen-fellowship.html','','','فرصت مطالعات و پژوهش  در دو سطح : پسا دکتری 6-24 ماه و محققین با تجربه 6-18 ماه. پوشش هزینه از 3205 تا 5320 یورو در ماه. نرخ پذیرش حدود 40%      ','',6),(422,'2017-03-05 11:10:04','2017-03-05 11:10:04','Bessel Research Award',4,NULL,'Scientists and scholars from abroad, internationally renowned in their field, who completed their doctorates less than 18 years ago and who in future are expected to continue producing cutting-edge achievements which will have a seminal influence on their discipline beyond their immediate field of work, are eligible to be nominated for a Friedrich Wilhelm Bessel Research Award.\nAward winners are honoured for their outstanding research record and invited to spend a period of up to one year cooperating on a long-term research project with specialist colleagues at a research institution in Germany. The stay may be divided up into blocks.\nThe Humboldt Foundation grants about 20 Friedrich Wilhelm Bessel Research Awards annually.\nNominations may be submitted by established academics in Germany. Nominations may also be initiated by award winners of the Humboldt Foundation working abroad, provided that the nomination is made jointly with a colleague working in Germany. Direct applications are not accepted. The award is valued at €45,000.','up to 1 year, can be devided in blocks','45','1. The nominee must be recognised internationally as an outstanding researcher in his/her field (e.g. awards, positive responses to publications, etc.).\n2. Expectation that the nominee will continue to produce cutting-edge achievementswhich will have a seminal influence on the discipline.\n3. Doctorate completed less than 18 years ago.\n4. Detailed expert opinion by an academic working at a research institution in Germany who would like to invite the nominee to spend time researching in Germany.\n5. Two expert reviews by important international and one from German collaborative partners and/or academics.\n\n','no dead line, each year they will have 2 Committees\n\n','https://www.humboldt-foundation.de/web/bessel-award.html','','','این حمایت برای مدت یک سال و به میزان 45 هزار یورو است. حدود 20 نفر در هر سال واجد شرایط می‌شوند. فاقد تاریخ اقدام است و ازاین‌جهت مناسب هست. استاد اقدام کننده می‌بایست از افراد مشهور و سرشناسی باشد که بیش از 18 سال از دریافت دکتری وی نگذشته باشد. طرح ارائه‌شده باید موجب جابه‌جایی حداقلی در مرزهای دانش شود. همچنین حمایت‌های جنبی نظیر دوره‌های آموزش زبان و (هزینه سفر نهایتاً هزار یورو یک‌بار در سال) نیز در نظر گرفته ‌شده است. دعوت توسط استاد آلمانی شروع میشود.','',6),(423,'2017-03-05 11:10:04','2017-03-05 11:10:04','Alexander von Humboldt Professorship\n',3,NULL,'International Award for Research in Germany\nAcademics of all disciplines from abroad, who are internationally recognised as leaders in their field and who are expected to contribute to enhancing Germany\\\'s sustained international competitiveness as a research location in consequence of the award, are eligible to be nominated for an Alexander von Humboldt Professorship.\nThe Alexander von Humboldt Professorship, which is financed by the Federal Ministry of Education and Research through the International Research Fund for Germany, enables award winners to carry out long-term and ground-breaking research at universities and research institutions in Germany. The award funds, totalling €5 million for academics in experimental disciplines and €3.5 million for researchers in theoretical disciplines, are made available for a period of five years.\nNominations may be made by German universities; non-university research institutions may also submit nominations jointly with a German university.\n','short-term, long-term and ground-breaking research- up to 5 yaers','Up to 180,000 EUR p. a. ---Monthly sum from the award funds: totaling 1/12 of the yearly salary for his or her personal income. ---Other income, including additional salary payments by the receiving institution or from third parties, will not be set against this.','\n1. The nominee must be recognised as a world leader in his or her field.\n2. The nominee must be established as an academic abroad.\n3. Nomination by a research institution entitled to make nominations.\n4. Detailed statement on the nominee\\\'s academic qualifications and his/her compatibility with the nominating university’s strategic development by the institution in Germany making the nomination.\n5. The nominating institution\\\'s strategic development plan, e.g., with regard to enhancing its capacity to compete internationally in the nominee\\\'s subject area as well as the nominee’s role as a catalyst in bringing about structural change.\n6. Assurance that the position can be sustainably integrated in the structure of the research institution even after Alexander von Humboldt Foundation sponsorship has come to an end\n\n','15 April and 15 October--- Reviewing the nominations takes five to six months','https://www.humboldt-foundation.de/web/alexander-von-humboldt-professorship.html','','','برنامه‌ای برای اساتید مطرح و با قابلیت هدایت یک تیم در سطح جهانی. این حمایت جهت کارهای پژوهشی است. سقف 180 هزار یورو در هر سال برای یک پروژه در نظر گرفته شده است. این هزینه شامل همه هزینه‌ی حقوق و سفر و تجهیزات و ... است. 1/12 یعنی نهایتاً 15 هزار یورو می‌تواند به‌عنوان حقوق استاد در هر سال نظر گرفته شود. پروژه می‌تواند در کل تا 5 سال تمدید شود. در کل این برنامه برای اساتیدی که پروژه خاصی دارند که هزینه‌بر است و قصد دارند پروژه را به اتمام برسانند بسیار عالی است ولی اساتیدی که صرفاً به دنبال درآمد ماهانه در قبال امور پژوهشی باشند این برنامه مناسبشان نیست. حتماً کسانی که برنامه خاصی دارند اقدام کنند نه آن دسته از اساتیدی که می‌خواهند در یک کار شریک شوند. دریافت هزینه از سایر منابع و حتی موسسه تحت عناوین دیگر هیچ ارتباطی یه این حمایت ندارد و مانع نمی‌شود؛ بنابراین می‌توان ضمن استفاده از این حمایت برای انجام پروژه، با موسسه/دانشگاه صحبت نمود تا سهم دریافتی استاد نیز به نحو بهتری تأمین شود. همچنین حمایت‌های جنبی نظیر دوره‌های آموزش زبان و (هزینه سفر نهایتاً هزار یورو یک‌بار در سال) نیز در نظر گرفته شده است. دعوت توسط استاد آلمانی شروع میشود.','',6),(424,'2017-03-05 11:13:25','2017-03-05 11:13:25','Horizon 2020',4,NULL,'Horizon 2020 is the biggest EU Research and Innovation programme ever with nearly €80 billion of funding available over 7 years (2014 to 2020) – in addition to the private investment that this money will attract. It promises more breakthroughs, discoveries and world-firsts by taking great ideas from the lab to the market.','Depends on the call','Depends on the call','2 EU partners ','Depends on the call','http://ec.europa.eu/research/participants/portal/desktop/en/home.html','','','این گرنت از طرف اتحادیه اروپا برای تحقیقاتی که برای اروپا مفید باشد با همکاری کشورهای غیراروپایی تخصیص داده می شود. وبسایت این گرنت در هر زمان موارد جدید را می گذارد که اساتید متقاضی می توانند برای آن مورد خاص اقدام کنند. برای اقدام همکاری دو کشور عضو اتحادیه اروپالازم است','',7),(426,'2017-03-05 11:17:25','2017-03-05 11:17:25','MSCA Co-funding of regional, national and international programmes (COFUND)',3,NULL,'COFUND offers additional funding for new or existing regional, national and international research mobility programmes to provide an international and intersectoral dimension to research training and career development. Doctoral programmes as well as fellowship programmes for experienced researchers can be supported. This action is meant for organisations that fund or manage doctoral programmes or fellowship programmes for researchers.\nEach COFUND proposal should have a sole participant, which could be a government ministry, regional authority, funding agency, university, research organisation, research academy or enterprise.','','','','','http://ec.europa.eu/research/mariecurieactions/about/cofunding_en','https://euraxess.ec.europa.eu/','','به نظر می آید این گرنت برای موسسات اروپایی باشد. ولی خود اساتید به تنهایی می توانند از لینک دوم برای فرصت های تبادل موجود در اروپا اقدام کنند. ','',7),(427,'2017-03-05 11:17:25','2017-03-05 11:17:25','MSCA Research and Innovation Staff Exchange (RISE)',6,NULL,'funds short-term exchanges for staff to develop careers combining scientific excellence with exposure to other countries and sectors. RISE enables more interaction between academia and non-academic organisations within Europe and worldwide. Proposals should include at least three partners, which can be universities, research institutions, or non-academic organisations.\nThe grant supports the secondment of staff members for one month to one year. They must be engaged in or linked to research and innovation activities for at least six months prior to the secondment.','Funding for a RISE project can last up to four years.','','Partner organisations should be from three different countries','','http://ec.europa.eu/research/mariecurieactions/about/research-innovation-staff-exchange_en','http://ec.europa.eu/research/participants/portal/desktop/en/opportunities/h2020/index.html','','دانشگاه می تواند برای این گرنت با مشارکت حداقل 2 موسسه اروپایی از دو کشور مختلف دیگر اقدام کند تا اساتیدش بتوانند برای تحقیقات کوتاه مدت به آن 2 موسسه سفر کنند. لینک دوم شامل لیستی از call هاست که دانشگاه باید برای یکی از آنها اقدام کند. ','',7),(428,'2017-03-05 11:17:25','2017-03-05 11:17:25','MSCA Innovative Training Networks (ITN)',6,NULL,'doctoral-level training in and outside academia which have 3 types: 1) European Training Networks in an organization based in EU 2)European Industrial Doctorates awarding doctoral degree 3) European Joint Doctorates awarding double or multiple PhD degrees from a minimum of 3 EU organizations\nThis action is meant primarily for organisations such as universities, research centres or companies, that propose a research training network. Mobility across borders is a must.\nGrants cover:\nrecruitment and training of each researcher for up to three years. The researcher is hired under an employment contract and benefits from a monthly living allowance, social security cover, a mobility and family allowance.\nresearch costs including the organisation of joint activities and conferences.\nmanagement and overhead costs.','4 years','','PhD Candidates, PhD Students, Post-docs, Prof.','','http://ec.europa.eu/research/participants/portal/desktop/en/opportunities/h2020/index.html','http://ec.europa.eu/research/mariecurieactions/about/innovative-training-networks_en','','دانشگاه می تواند برای این گرنت اقدام کند تا تبادل دانشجوی دکتری یا استاد بین موسسات را با کشورهای اروپایی داشته باشد. برای اقدام باید از طریق لینک اول برای یک call for proposal اقدام کرد.','',7),(429,'2017-03-05 11:17:25','2017-03-05 11:17:25','MSCA  Individual Fellowships (IF)',6,NULL,'Individual Fellowships fund researchers looking to enhance their career development and prospects by working abroad. Mobility across borders is a must. Cross-sectoral mobility is also encouraged. \nThe grant is awarded to your host organisation.\nProposals are submitted in reply to a call for proposals. Submit a research proposal, including your CV. The proposal is written jointly with your chosen host organisation(s) (a university, a research centre or a company).','European Fellowships last from one to two years, Global Fellowships from two to three years.','allowance to cover your living, travel and family costs','Prof.','','http://ec.europa.eu/research/mariecurieactions/about/individual-fellowships_en','http://ec.europa.eu/research/participants/portal/desktop/en/opportunities/h2020/index.html','','اساتید دانشگاه می توانند برای فرصت مطالعاتی یا تحقیقاتی از این گرنت استفاده کنند. برای اقدام باید از طریق لینک دوم یک فرصت مناسب را انتخاب کنند و با همکاریدانشگاه یا موسسه تحقیقاتی میزبان در اروپا برای آن فرصت اقدام کنند. ','',7),(430,'2017-03-05 11:17:26','2017-03-05 11:17:26','Marie Skłodowska-Curie actions - Research Fellowship Programme (MSCA)',4,NULL,'The MSCA support research training and career development focused on innovation skills, irrespective of nationality. Supports industrial doctorates. Scientists have the possibility to gain experience abroad and in the private sector. Fosters mobility between countries','','','PhD Candidates, PhD Students, Post-docs, Prof.','','','','','ناقص','undone - tag',7),(431,'2017-03-05 11:18:43','2017-03-05 11:18:43','Helmholtz Research Schools',3,NULL,'Helmholtz Research Schools are small units of up to 25 PhD students and their supervisors focused on specific research topics.  They provide a highly collaborative, internationalized and invigorating interdisciplinary learning environment for talented researchers.   Helmholtz Research Schools are often part of the larger Helmholtz Graduate Schools .\nEach Helmholtz Research School has its own selection procedure to ensure that, in its field, the student is a good match with their supervisory team.\nThe Helmholtz Research Schools and Graduate Schools oﬀer structured doctoral programmes for highly qualifed PhD students in partnership with universities. Young researchers gain considerable experience of close research cooperation between work groups.\n\nApplications should be submitted to the respective Helmholtz Research School or Graduate School. The individual schools advertise their vacancies or set application deadlines. You will fnd links to the diﬀerent schools on the programme website','Generally 3 years with possible extension by 1 year.','Work contract (usually part-time); the salary is based on the collective agreement for public sector employees (currently between 3,400 and 3,800 euros per month gross for a full-time position). Individual schools can also award scholarships.','PhD students with\n1.an outstanding university degree equivalent to a German Master’s degree\n2.an academic qualifcation in an appropriate subject for the respective research institute\n3. previous research experience\n4.a relevant PhD research proposal for the respective research group\n5.a good knowledge of the English language','depends','https://www.helmholtz.de/en/jobs_talent/funding_programs/doctoral_students/','http://www.imd.kit.edu/','','واحدهای کوچک (به عنوان بخشی از graduate schools)هستند که بر اساس شش فیلد اصلی این موسسه تا ظرفیت 25 دانشجوی دکتری می پذیرند.\nهر یک از این مراکز قوانین و روال خاص خود را در خصوص انتخاب داوطلبان دارد.\nداوطلبان می بایست به از طریق وبسایت واحد های هلم هولتز و با توجه به زمان های ثبت نام اقدام نمایند.\nداوطلبان می بایست پروپوزالی مرتبط با گروهی که تمایل دارند برا ی آن اقدام نمایند داشته باشند.\nبرای زمینه های پژوهشی تخصصی تر و برای پژوهشگرانی پروپوزال های قوی تری دارند.','',8),(432,'2017-03-05 11:18:43','2017-03-05 11:18:43','HelmHoltz Graduate Schools',3,NULL,'Helmholtz Graduate Schools have broad subject areas (such as \\\'Energy\\\', which could cover nuclear safety to photovoltaics and the mathematics of power grid models).  The Graduate Schools can have anything from 150 to 250 students.  Often, the Helmholtz Research Schools (see above) are part of the Graduate School. The curricula for the Schools is varied and interdisciplinarity is highly encouraged.  \n\nAll \\\'students\\\' are funded (mostly receiving a salary, and there are no PhD fees).  PhDs are awarded by partner universities.  The standard of PhD supervision is high at the Helmholtz Association and is designed not only to provide an excellent scientific training but also training in transferable skills (such as business planning, project management and writing skills). \nThe Helmholtz Research Schools and Graduate Schools oﬀer structured doctoral programmes for highly qualifed PhD students in partnership with universities. Young researchers gain considerable experience of close research cooperation between work groups.\n\nApplications should be submitted to the respective Helmholtz Research School or Graduate School. The individual schools advertise their vacancies or set application deadlines. You will fnd links to the diﬀerent schools on the programme website','Generally 3 years with possible extension by 1 year.','Work contract (usually part-time); the salary is based on the collective agreement for public sector employees (currently between 3,400 and 3,800 euros per month gross for a full-time position). Individual schools can also award scholarships.','PhD students with\n1.an outstanding university degree equivalent to a German Master’s degree\n2.an academic qualifcation in an appropriate subject for the respective research institute\n3. previous research experience\n4.a relevant PhD research proposal for the respective research group\n5.a good knowledge of the English language','depends','https://www.helmholtz.de/en/jobs_talent/funding_programs/doctoral_students/','http://macrobio.hzg.de/054706/index_0054706.html.de','','این واحد ها ممکن است در  زمینه های متفاوتی  و با همکاری دانشگاه های خاص فعالیت نمایند. و ممکن است بین 150 تا 250 نفر دانشجو داشته باشند.\nهمه دانشجو ها از فاند استفاده می کنند.\nدر زمان مقرر مدارک مورد نیاز را برای موسسه مربوطه ارسال می نمایند.\nرو موضوع بزرگ و کلی تر کار می کنند و می توانند از چند موسسه تحقیقاتی استفاده می کنند و با دانشگاه های ارائه کننده مدرک دکترا برای این رشته ها همکاری می نمایند. ','',8),(433,'2017-03-05 11:18:43','2017-03-05 11:18:43','HelmHoltz Juniors',5,NULL,'Helmholtz Juniors (HeJu) is an initiative launched by doctoral students and PhD candidates in the Helmholtz Association which fosters exchange and networking among peers, represents the view of PhD students to their respective management committees and expand the range of advanced training opportunities available to them.\n\nA Helmholtz Juniors group is made up of at least two PhD student representatives from each Helmholtz Centre. Since students tyically spend three years working on their theses, the representatives change almost every year, giving new representatives the opportunity to be involved in the development of PhD training. \nMost Helmholtz Centres elect two PhD-student representatives for a term of one year, who then automatically become members of the Helmholtz Juniors who represent the view os students to the Helmholtz Association management team. \n\nSome larger Helmholtz Research Centres (for instance, those with perhaps over 250 PhD students) have their own representative bodies and two representatives from these bodies become HeJu members. ','1 year','','being a PhD students at Helmhltz one of the Helmholtz Centers','\n','https://www.helmholtz.de/en/jobs_talent/funding_programs/doctoral_students/','https://www.helmholtz.de/en/jobs_talent/funding_programs/doctoral_students/helmholtz_juniors/','','این گروه ها از حداقل 2 دانشجوی دکترا به عنوان نماینده از هر مرکز هلم هولتز تشکیل شده است.\nبا توجه به اینکه دانشجویان دکترا به سه سال زمان نیاز دارند، این نمایندگان ممکن است هر ساله تغییر کنند.\nبیشتر مراکز هلم هولتز سالانه 2 دانشجوی دکتری را به عنوان نماینده انتخاب می کنند که به صورت اتوماتیک عضو این گروه می شوند و در واقع نماینده نظرات دانشجویان مرکز هلم هولتز می شوند.','undone - tag',8),(434,'2017-03-05 11:18:43','2017-03-05 11:18:43','Helmholtz Young Investigators Groups',6,NULL,'Helmholtz Young Investigator Groups (YIGs) are formed by granting an outstanding postdoctoral researcher €300,000 annual funding for five years to create a new research group. The grant is awarded through a competitive call early in each year.\nThe main criterion for receiving the grant is having a proposal which demonstrates scientific excellence in one of the Helmholtz Association\\\'s six fields of research. \n\nYoung Investigator Group leaders are encouraged to develop the academic independence which secures their long-term career.  YIGs have been funded by the Initiative and Networking Fund (or President\\\'s Strategic Fund) since 2003.  About 200 early career researchers have won funding for their ideas.  Most of the awards have gone to foreigners or Germans returning from an extended research appointment abroad.  It is important for prospective applicants to consider whether or not their research profile is sufficiently international.\n\nNote: the Helmholtz Research Centres are also host to junior research group leaders who gain their funding from other sources (for example, the DFG).  There is a strong community of junior research group leaders within the Helmholtz Association as a whole.','5-6 years','€300,000 annual funding for five years','Researchers with between two- and six-years\\\' postdoctoral experience are eligible to apply.The six-year limit may be extended in certain circumstances, for instance for parental leave or where the subject subject requires a researcher to be dual qualified in medicine and scientific research).','early in each year','https://www.helmholtz.de/en/jobs_talent/funding_programs/helmholtz_young_investigators_groups/','','','این گروه ها با اهدای فاند به مبلغ 300 هزار یورو سالانه و تا مدت 5 سال به پژوهشگران پسا دکترا برای تشکیل گروه های پژوهشی جدید، تشکیل می شود.\nفاند به صورت رقابتی در فراخوان های سالانه تخصیص می یابد. متقاضیان می بایست فعالیت بین المللی داشته باشند.\nمعیار اصلی برای دریافت فاند نیز ارائه پروپوزال سطح عالی در یکی از شش زمینه اصلی پژوهش های هلم هولتز می باشد.\nمراکز هلم هولتزهمچنین میتوانند میزبان فردی که از موسسات دیگر به عنوان مثال دی اف جی فاند برای سرپستی گروه های پژوهشی دریافت نموده است، باشند.',' ERROR-NO Tag',8),(435,'2017-03-05 11:18:43','2017-03-05 11:18:43','HelmHoltz Professorships (W2/W3-Program)',3,NULL,'the Helmholtz Association is committed to increasing female representation in senior researcher positions.\n\nUnder the W2/W3 (German professorial grades) programme for excellent female scientists five W2/W3 positions a year can be funded by the President’s Strategic Fund. The positions are funded for five years which typically amounts to €1m annually for W3 posts and €750,000 for W2 posts.\n\nManagement Boards from the respective Helmholtz Centres are entitled to apply.  \nW3 = professor \nW2 = although paid like a professor appointed at level W2, lecturers in this position do not have a professor title; the term was formerly used in other states for lecturer positions with research and teaching responsibilities','5 years ',' €1m (200,000 EUR annually) for W3 posts \n €750,000 (150,000 EUR annually) for W2 posts.','','last deadline was Aug. 1 2016','https://www.helmholtz.de/en/jobs_talent/funding_programs/helmholtz_professorships_w2w3_programme/','','','این فاند جهت افزایش حضور زنان در سمت‌های ارشد در تحقیقات می‌باشد. \nتحت طرح برنامه عالی برای دانشمندان زن  پنج موقعیت در هر سال پوشش داده می‌شود. به طور معمول این پست 5 ساله می‌باشد که کسانی که پست W3  را دارند سالانه 1 میلیون یورو و کسانی که پست W2 دارند سالانه 750 هزار یورو تامین می‌شوند. \nW3 و W2 رده بندی استادی در آلمان می‌باشد ','',8),(436,'2017-03-05 11:18:44','2017-03-05 11:18:44','Helmholtz ERC Recognition Award',3,NULL,'Researchers who submitted a proposal for ERC 2016 StG or EC 2016 CoG within the framework of Horizon 2020 and who were then invited to an interview, proving the excellence of the researcher and the proposal, can apply for a grant of up to € 200,000 from the Helmholtz Association’s Initiative and Networking Fund. All applicants who reached Step 2, but were subsequently not awarded an ERC grant are eligible. The grant is accompanied by the condition that the applicant must resubmit the ERC application within 24 months of the begin of the funding period and that a Helmholtz Centre is once more the hosting institution. Funding is designed to support the resubmitting of applications in response to one of the next appropriate ERC calls. Funding is open to applicants who are already employed at a Helmholtz Centre or submitted their original proposal via a Helmholtz Centre as host institution respectively.\n','2 years ','up to  200,000 EUR','1. Formal application by the authorised department of the Helmholtz Centre, using the template provided,\n2. letter from the ERC showing the evaluation results at Step 2, and the final evaluation report for the project proposal,\n3. complete official version of the proposal submitted to the ERC,\n4. brief description of the proposed use of the award \n','May 31st, 2017\n','https://www.helmholtz.de/en/jobs_talent/funding_programs/promoting_scientists_on_an_international_level/helmholtz_erc_recognition_award/','','','برای پشتیبانی از پروپوزال های برجسته بورس  ERC  که در چارچوب هورایزن 2020 و از طریق مرکز تحقیقات هلممولتز پروپوزال خود را ارائه داده اند می‌باشد.  ','',8),(437,'2017-03-05 11:18:44','2017-03-05 11:18:44','Helmholtz International Fellow Award',3,NULL,'For Excellent Researchers and Science Managers from abroad \noutstanding senior scientists and research managers based outside Germany who have excelled in fields relevant to the Helmholtz Association, including science management at large international research institutions.\nThe award will give Helmholtz International Fellows the opportunity to pursue research flexibly at one or more Helmholtz Centres where cooperation already exists or would be useful and profitable in the future. Up to 10 Helmholtz International Fellow Awards can be awarded each year. Nominations can be submitted anytime by all member institutions of the Helmholtz Association. \nthe award must be accepted personally by the\naward winner. The award is not transferable. Helmholtz International Fellows may use the funding to cover the costs of their stay in Germany (e.g. for travel and accommodation costs).\nThey are free to use the funding flexibly and however they like. ','Visiting researchers will arrange a starting date for their stay in consultation with the host\nresearchers / Helmholtz Centres in Germany. The duration of the research period will depend\non the relevant requirements and conditions of the planned research cooperation and will also\nbe agreed between the successful candidate and their host. If desired, the research period\ncan be divided into several short-term stays.','the monetary value of the award will be stated in the award letter upon the candidate\\\'s acceptance ','The most important criteria are the researcher’s academic performance and the compatibility of\nhis/her research field or project with the activities of the proposed Helmholtz Centre. Priority\nwill be given to individuals who are already working successfully with the Helmholtz Centres.\nIn 2016 up to 10 Helmholtz International Fellow Awards can be awarded. The Helmholtz\nInternational Fellow Award provides funding of €20,000. German or international researchers\nwho are based abroad and who do not have an employment contract with a Helmholtz Centre\nare eligible for funding.','Applications may be submitted at any time (at least 6 weeks in advance of the counsil meetings)\nnote that counsil meeting deadlines are announced yearly  ','http://www.helmholtz.de/en/aktuell/current_calls_for_applications/artikel/artikeldetail/helmholtz_international_fellow_award/','https://www.helmholtz.de/fileadmin/user_upload/06_jobs_talente/Ausschreibungen/International_Fellow_Award/Call-for-Nominations_Helmholtz-International-Fellow-Award-2016.pdf','','برای محققان بسیار عالی و مدیران علوم از خارج از کشور\nدانشمندان برجسته ارشد و مدیران پژوهش خارج از آلمان که در زمینه های مربوط به انجمن هلمهولتز، از جمله مدیریت علوم در موسسات تحقیقاتی بزرگ بین المللی برجسته هستند.\nاین بورسیه این فرصت را به محققین میدهد تا در یک یا چند مراکز هلمهولتز که در آن همکاری قبلا وجود داشته یا مفید و سودمند خواهد بود کار کنند.  درخواست کننده میتواند  طبق زمان فراخوان در هر زمانی پروپوزال خود را به موسسه ارسال نماید. \nمبلغ بورس پس از پذیرفته شدن درخواست در نامه ابلاغ خواهد داده شد. \n','',8),(438,'2017-03-05 11:18:44','2017-03-05 11:18:44','Helmholtz Mentoring Program',3,NULL,'The Helmholtz Mentoring Programme for young women working at the Helmholtz Association, \\\'Taking the Lead\\\', is part of the Association’s equal opportunities strategy. It aims to raise the number of women in executive-level positions, where they are still significantly under-represented.\nThe programme is aimed at early career women with between two to five years\\\' postdoctoral experience and women working in administration and management at the beginning of their careers and who aspire to executive-level positions. All participants must be Helmholtz Research Centre staff.','','','','','','','','ناقص','undone - tag',8),(439,'2017-03-05 11:18:44','2017-03-05 11:18:44','Helmholtz Work Placement Program',3,NULL,'The Helmholtz Work Placement Programme offers young leaders in science and administration, or technical experts working at Helmholtz Centres, a chance to spend several months at other institutions to expand and develop their skills. It addresses the increasing importance of creating exceptionally well-educated and qualified technical and administrative staff at the Helmholtz Association.\nThe programme will focus on funding work placements in institutions abroad to ensure participants gain experience of working in an international context. \nThe selected participants will be released on sabbatical by their Helmholtz Centres for up to twelve months, with continuing payment of salary, in order to allow them to complete work placements at ministries or other research and scientific institutions. The individual placements should be between three and twelve months long. Each participant should spend at least six months on placement – if they wish by carrying out two three-month placements at two different institutions.','','','','next call in 2017','','','','ناقص','undone - tag',8),(440,'2017-03-05 11:20:20','2017-03-05 11:20:20','Program description',1,NULL,'Max 3 months for research visits, Max 12 months ','','holding a doctorate, working at a German research institution','No Submission Deadline','http://www.dfg.de/en/research_funding/programmes/international_cooperation/initiation_international_collaboration/in_brief/index.html','http://www.dfg.de/foerderung/programme/internationale_programme/aufbau_internationaler_kooperationen/formulare_merkblaetter/index.jsp','','با استفاده از این فاند می توان اقدام به برگزاری کارگاه، انجام سفرهای خارجی برای المانی ها و همچنین دعوت از همکاران برای سفر به آلمان نمود.\nمی بایست همواره این مساله را در نظر داشت که پروژه ها فقط میتواند از سوی فرد آلمانی در بنیاد پژوهش آلمان ثبت و بررسی گردد. برای دریافت نتیجه مطلوب لازم است برای استفاده از فاند در زمان مطلوب حدود 6 ماه قبل اقدام شود.این فاند برای مبالغ بالای 20 هزار یورو حداقل به سه ماه زمان برای ارزیابی نیاز دارد.','  2.7, 2.9, 3.5, 3.7','undone - tag',9),(441,'2017-03-05 11:20:20','2017-03-05 11:20:20','Cooperation with Develoing Country',3,NULL,'The DFG funds research projects conducted by scientists in Germany in cooperation with scientists in developing countries.\n The objective is to promote cooperation between researchers in Germany and in developing countries. In a research project on a specifically defined topic within a limited time period.\n\nFunding for personnel, scientific instrumentation and apparatus, consumables, travel, miscellaneous expenses and publications for both the partner institute in Germany and the cooperation partner/institute in the developing country.\n','\nthere seems to be no time limit ','','Researchers/scientists from all subjects and disciplines at German research institutions who have completed their academic education (typically by having completed a doctorate). ','No Submission Deadline','http://www.dfg.de/en/research_funding/programmes/international_cooperation/developing_countries/in_brief/index.html','','','این فاند به پروژه های تحقیقاتی که توسط دانشمندان آلمانی که با همکاری افرادی از کشورهای در حال توسعه هدایت میشود تعلق می گیرد و مواردی از قبیل پرسنل، تجهیزات آزمایشگاهی هزینه های سفر و غیره را شامل میشود.\nفاند هم به موسسه تحقیقاتی آلمانی و هم موسسه تحقیقاتی کشور در حال توسعه تعلق می گیرد.\n','',9),(442,'2017-03-05 11:20:20','2017-03-05 11:20:20','Mercator Fellow',3,NULL,'\nFellowships enable intensive, long-term project-based collaboration between researchers from both domestic and foreign institutions. Although Mercator Fellows are on-site for only part of the project, they remain in contact with the project team members once their research stay is over. Foreign Mercator Fellowship holders are awarded the title of Mercator Fellows in recognition of their dedication.\n\nWhat’s new is that the Mercator Fellowship can now be applied for as part of project funding by researchers in Germany. Alternatively, the module can also be applied for on behalf of the project teams by the coordinators of Research Units and Priority Programmes. To be eligible, the Mercator Fellow must contribute to attaining the project’s objective. This means that projects in which the Mercator Fellow plays a central role are also eligible.','The length of the research stay is not specified. Depending on the project’s needs and the availability of the Mercator Fellow, either one extended stay, e.g. a semester or a year, or several shorter stays are possible.','Fellows can receive a salary according to their qualification. Additionally, they will receive an allowance to cover travel expenses.','Applications for a Mercator Fellowship will only be accepted for researchers working at a German research institution. The application will be within the framework of a larger comprehensive application in one of the DFG’s programs','No Submission Deadline','www.dfg.de/en/mercator','','','این فاند مورد استفاده برای پژوهشگران و جهت همکاری در همکاری های پروژه محور باند مدت چه در آلمان و چه در کشور های دیگر می باشد.\nاگرچه این محققین برتر تنها در بخشی از پروژه در محل انجام پروژه حضور دارند ولی با تیم تا انتهای پروژه در ارتباط خواهند بود.\nتقاضای این فاند تنها برای پژوهشگرانی که در موسسه تحقیقاتی آلمانی مشغول به کار یاشند امکان پذیر است.\nمدت حضور محقق هم میتواند یک اقامت بلند مدت و یا چند اقامت کوتاه مدت باشد.\nدستمزد بر اساس کفایت پژوهشگر اختصاص می یابد و هزینه های سفر را نیز پوشش می دهد.\n','',9),(443,'2017-03-05 11:20:20','2017-03-05 11:20:20','Emmy Noether Program',3,NULL,'The DFG supports research in higher education and public research institutions.\nThis program enables outstanding postdocs/junior researchers to rapidly qualify for leading positions in science and research or for a university teaching career by heading an independent junior research group and assuming relevant teaching duties.\n','Generally 5 years (maximum of 6 years).','Funding for an independent junior research group; includes supervisory salary and covers expenses for staff and consumables necessary to complete the project during the funding period.','\nApplicants must have international research experience.\nAs a rule, researchers who have acquired between two and four years of postdoctoral research experience are eligible to apply.\nCandidates are expected to have an excellent research project and at least 2 years and up to a maximum of 4 years (medical researchers: up to 6 years) of postdoctoral experience including substantial international research experience; foreign applicants are eligible if they intend to continue their research career in Germany following completion at the end of the funding period.','No Submission Deadline',' www.dfg.de/emmy_noether/en','','','این فاند می تواند در همه رشته ها به داوطلبین بین سالهای 2 و چهارم پسا دکترا که حداقل دو سال سابقه فعالیت بین المللی دارند تعلق می گیرد.\nمحققین غیر آلمانی می بایست پس پایان دوره تحقیقاتی تحت حمایت فاند، فعالیت علمی خود را در آلمان ادامه دهند.(این مساله باید توسط متقاضی فاند در پروپوزال قید شود)\nفاند برای Junior Research Group مستقل شامل شامل حقوق دستمزد سرپرستی شده و هزینه های پرسنل و تجهیزات مصرفی مورد نیاز را در طی دوره فاند شامل می شود.\n','',9),(444,'2017-03-05 11:20:20','2017-03-05 11:20:20','International Research Training Groups',3,NULL,'International Research Training Groups provide opportunities for joint doctoral training programmes between German universities and universities abroad. The research and study programmes are jointly developed and supervised. Doctoral students in the programme complete a six-month research stay at the respective partner institution.\nto stablish an IRTG, 5-10 faculty members are needed per side (Germany, abroad) who want to collaborate on an interdisciplinary research focus with a joint program.\n\n','two 4.5-year cycle(max. 9 years) for research training groups & 3-year terms for doctoral positions, including 6 months stay at partner institutions','IRTG offer funding to doctoral researchers, postdocs, visiting researchers, and researcher students and cover expenses for travel, workshops, small equipment, consumable, cooordination, …','Universities or Equivalent Higher Education Institutions','No Submission Deadline','http://www.dfg.de/en/research_funding/programmes/coordinated_programmes/research_training_groups/international_rtg/index.html','http://www.dfg.de/en/research_funding/programmes/list/index.jsp?id=GRK','','این فاند به منظور ایجاد دوره های مشترک دکترا با همکاری دانشگاه های آلمانی و دانشگاه های دیگر کشور هاست اولویت با رشته جدید ترکیبی می باشد.\n دانشجویان دکترای این دوره می بایست یه دوره شش ماهه را در موسسه همکار سپری کنند.\n جهت انجام دوره لازم  5-10 نفر از هر طرف جهت برای تشکیل گروه جهت همکاری بر روی پروژه حضور یابند.',' ERROR-NO Tag',9),(445,'2017-03-05 11:20:20','2017-03-05 11:20:20','Research Units',3,NULL,'Funding for a Research Unit enables researchers to collaborate closely on specific medium-term projects whose anticipated findings could not be achieved within the scope of the Research Grants Programme. \nA Research Unit typically has fewer than ten projects which are coordinated to enable work on a common research topic.\nA proposal for a Research Unit is submitted jointly by several researchers who work in Germany or at a German research institution abroad and have completed their academic training (usually with a doctorate).\nParticipation by researchers based outside Germany is possible if their project is of added value to the Research Unit at large. This must be explained in the proposal.\nIn general, you are not eligible to submit a proposal if you work at an institution that is not non-profit or one that does not allow immediate publication of research findings in a generally accessible form.\nEmmy Noether Independent Junior Research Groups and Heisenberg grant holders may be associated in Research Units.','6 years or 8 years in exceptional cases.\nThe first funding period is generally three years. Further funding requires the submission and approval of renewal proposals.','','Outstanding researchers\nScientific quality and originality of a research project at an international level','No Submission Deadline','http://www.dfg.de/en/research_funding/programmes/coordinated_programmes/research_units/in_brief/index.html','','','Research Unit تیمی متشکل از پژوهشگرانی است که بر روی پروژه ای تحقیقاتی کار می کنند که از حیث تمرکز موضوعی، زمان و بعد مالی نمی تواند از حمایت های مالی فاند های Individual Grants Programme و Priority Programme استفاده نماید. کیفیت و نوآوری پروژه تحقیقاتی در سطح بین الملل از الزامات استفاده از این فاند است.\nResearch Unit کارکنان و مواد مورد نیاز برای انجام پروژه های فشرده و یا بلند مدت را تا حدود 6 سال فراهم می نماید.\nپروپوزال برای این فاند به صورت مشترک توسط چند پژوهشگر در آلمان و یا موسسه تحقیقاتی آلمانی در خارج آلمان که دارای مدرک دکترا هستند ارائه می گردد. شرکت پژوهشگرانی غیر آلمانی در این طرح ها در صورتیکه طرح از اهمیت خاصی برخوردار باشد، امکان پذیر است. در صورتیکه پژوهشگران در موسسه ای کار می کنند که اجازه انتشار یافته های پژوهش در مراحل ابتدایی وجود نداشته باشد، امکان ارائه پروپوزال وجود ندارد.\nبرای دریافت فاند ابتدا می بایست پیش نویس پروپوزال جهت بررسی به دفتر مرکزی بنیاد پژوهش آلمان بررسی شود و در صورت تایید بنیاد از متقاضیان جهت ارائه پروپوزال کامل دعوت می نماید.',' ERROR-NO Tag',9),(446,'2017-03-05 11:20:20','2017-03-05 11:20:20','Priority Programmes',3,NULL,'A Priority Programme is a funding programme with an open call for proposals aimed at the following objectives:\nFunding  of  projects  characterised  by high  originality  and  quality in terms of their topic and/ or methodology.\n\nPriority Programmes will not be announced for research areas that are already well es-tablished and currently receive adequate funding from other sources.\nAdded value through interdisciplinary cooperation (interdisciplinarity)\nAdded value through cooperation between different locations (networking)\nSupport for early-career researchers participating in the projects\nGender equality measures tailored to the Priority Programme\nAll researchers who work in Germany or at a German research institution abroad and have completed their training, usually with a doctorate, are eligible to participate in the preparation of an establishment proposal.\n','A maximum of six years, basically split into two funding periods of three years each.\nAs a rule, Senate selection meetings are held in March of a given year. New programmes are established and project funding begins the year after this.','','','Proposals to establish a Priority Programme must be submitted by 15 October of a given year.','http://www.dfg.de/en/research_funding/programmes/coordinated_programmes/priority_programmes/in_brief/index.html','','','فاند به پروژه هاي تحقيقاتي با موضوعات و ايده هاي كاملا جديد و خلاقانه که تاثيري پايدار بر چشم انداز علمي داشته باشد، تعلق مي گيريد. نمایندگان بنیاد سالانه یک بار جهت انتخاب پروژه برگزیده برای این فاند جلسه ای برگزار می کنند و فاند از سال بعد از به پروژه تعلق می گیرد. حداکثر حمایت مالی برای 6 سال خواهد بود که که طی دو دوره 3 ساله انجام می گیرد.\nفاند به پروژه های تکراری و آنهایی که از فاند دیگری استفاده کرده اند تعلق نمی گیرد، بلکه به پروژه های که زمینه ای میان رشته ای دارند و از مکان های متفاوت در آن مشارکت و هدایت می شوند و با پروژه هایی که بانوان بدون تبعیض جنسیتی در آن  دخیلند نیز تعلق می گیرد. ',' ERROR-NO Tag',9),(447,'2017-03-05 11:20:20','2017-03-05 11:20:20','Individual Research Grants',3,NULL,'Researchers in Germany, or those working at a German research institution abroad, who have completed their academic training (a doctorate as a rule) are eligible to apply for DFG research grants.\nIn general you are not eligible to submit a proposal if you work at an institution that is not non-profit or one that does not allow immediate publication of research findings in a generally accessible form.\nAs part of your research grant proposal, you may submit one or more of the following modules.\nBasic Module: Use the basic module to request funding for direct project costs, project-specific staff, and instrumentation necessary to carry out the project.\nTemporary Positions for Principal Investigators: If you would like to propose a position for yourself as the leader of this project, use thismodule to request funding for your temporary position as principal investigator.\nReplacements : If your project requires that you be released from teaching or administrative duties, you can use this module to request funding for a replacement to take over these responsibilities.\nTemporary Substitutes for Clinicians: If this project requires that clinicians conduct research, you can use this module to request funding for temporary substitutes to take over their patient-care responsibilities.\nMercator Fellows: This module enables you to pursue an intensive and long-term exchange with researchers in Germany and abroad. Fellows will partially be on site but will remain in contact with you even after their stay.\nProject-Specific Workshops: If you would like to conduct workshops as part of your project, you may request funding to help you do so. Please note that this module cannot be submitted separately but only in conjunction with the proposed research project.\nPublic Relations: To enable you to present your work to the general lay public, you can request funding for public relations. Please note that this module cannot be submitted separately but only in conjunction with the proposed research project.','The maximum initial funding duration is three years. Subsequently, a renewal proposal may be submitted.\nThe duration of funding is based on the individual project needs (as a rule, several years).','','Qualified researchers (as a rule, those holding a doctorate) from all disciplines working at German research institutions\nA research project of high scientific quality and originality, carried out at an international level.\nResearchers working at institutions which serve purely commercial purposes or those who are not permitted to publish findings in a generally accessible form are not eligible to apply.','First proposal: No submission deadline\nRenewal proposal: At least 6 months before the approved funds have been completely used up.','http://www.dfg.de/en/research_funding/programmes/individual/research_grants/in_brief/index.html','','','پژوهشگران آلمانی و یا شاغل در یکی از موسسات آلمانی در بیرون این کشور که دارای مدرک دکترا می باشند می توانند برای دریافت این فاند اقدام نمایند.\nافراد در صورت اشتغال به کار در موسساتی بغیر از موسسات غیرانتفاعی یا موسساتی که اجازه انتشار یافته های علمی در مراحل اولیه پژوهش را نمی دهند، امکان ارائه پروپوزال ندارند.\nمدت زمان استفاده از فاند وابسته به طرح می باشد که در اولین فاز تا سه سال را شامل می شود.\n',' ERROR-NO Tag',9),(448,'2017-03-05 11:20:21','2017-03-05 11:20:21','Research Fellowships',3,NULL,'provided they have been resident in Germany for several years and have completed at least three years of scientific work as a doctoral or postdoctoral researcher in the German research system and state that they wish to continue to pursue their research in Germany in the future.\nFor the duration of the fellowship, recipients should not be required to carry out any work which is not directly relevant to the objective of the fellowship.\nFellowships are intended to cover the recipients’ costs of living and may not be used to supplement grants from other funding organisations or income from employment.','As a rule, up to 2 years ','Basic fellowship plus monthly lump sum payment to cover maintenance and travel costs\nForeign allowance Travel allowance, Publication costs,\nBenefits for fellowship recipients with children:   Children’s supplement\n170 Euro/m Basically-250 Euro','German researchers from all disciplines who have completed their academic qualifications (doctorate)\nInternational researchers from all disciplines who have completed their scientific training (doctorate)\nHigh scientific quality and originality of a research project at an international level ','No Submission Deadline','http://www.dfg.de/en/research_funding/programmes/individual/research_fellowships/in_brief/index.html','http://www.dfg.de/en/research_funding/programmes/individual/research_fellowships/calculator/index.jsp','لینک دوم مربوط به موتوری است که حدود هزینه پرداختی روبر اساس کشوری که فلو شیب در آن انجام می شود وضعیت تاهل و تعداد فرزند تخمین میزند','دارندگان مدرک دکترا که دارای اقامت چند ساله در کشور آلمان باشند وحداقل سه سال فعالیت پژوهشی به عنوان پژوهشگر دکترا و یا پسا دکترا در محیط پژوهشی آلمان داشته باشند.\nاین فاند به عنوان کمک هزینه زندگی برای شخص استفاده کننده می باشد و به عنوان مکمل برای فاند از دیگر موسسات نمی باشد.\nلازم به ذکر است افرادی که از کشوری غیر از آلمان پروپوزال ارائه می نمایند،می بایست بیشتر سال های تحصیلی خود را در کشور المان سپری کرده باشند و پس از پایان دکترا بیشتر از سه سال را در آن کشور خارجی سپری نکرده باشند و همچنین بیشتر از یکسال را در موسسه میزبان یه پژوهش نپرداخته باشند.\n\n',' ERROR-NO Tag',9),(449,'2017-03-05 11:20:21','2017-03-05 11:20:21','International Scienitific Events',4,NULL,'International specialist conferences: Integrative lecture event with a specific topic and focus on a European audience; a variant of the Gordon Conference\nInternational congress, symposium, colloquia, workshop: International scientific event of particular significance for a specific subject area with a large number of participants from both Germany and abroad; held in a different country each year\nAnnual meeting: A regularly recurring meeting of a German specialist society, working group or specialist group; event of national significance with a clearly defined topic and international participation.\n\nInternational specialist conferences: Funding can be provided to cover expenses remaining after all other financing opportunities have been exhausted.\nInternational congress, symposium, colloquia, workshop: Lump sum, varies according to the number of researchers participating\nAnnual meeting: Allowances for travel expenses (travel and maintenance costs) for active participants from abroad','','Staff costs, room rental (including utilities), instrumentation and equipment, printed materials, office supplies, postage costs, travel allowance (travel and accommodation costs)\nFor annual meetings: funding is provided only for travel expenses (rail or air) for roundtrip travel to the meeting, as well as maintenance costs for each day of the event','','Generally 6 months before the event begins. \nSpecial regulation for annual meetings: proposals can only be supported every second year. ','http://www.dfg.de/en/research_funding/programmes/international_cooperation/international_events/in_brief/index.html','','','جهت برگزاری کنفرانس، کارگاه و فعالیتهای مرتبط که مخاطب اصلی آن اروپایی‌ها می‌باشند. رویداد باید در کشور آلمان برگزار شود و تا 6 ماه قبل از شروع رویداد پروپوزال باید ارائه شود. \n','the event will have to take place in Germany ERROR-NO Tag',9),(450,'2017-03-05 11:20:21','2017-03-05 11:20:21','Collaborative Research Centers',3,NULL,'Collaborative Research Centres are long-term university-based research institutions, established for up to 12 years, in which researchers work together within a multidisciplinary research programme.\n\nCollaborative Research Centres consist of a large number of projects. The number and scope of these projects depend on the research programme. Individual projects are led by one researcher or jointly by several researchers.In addition, research partners from abroad may be integrated into a Collaborative Research Centre as principal investigators, either in individual projects or in the form of a foreign location as part of a CRC/Transregio. Prerequisites for this are research excellence, compelling thematic integration into the overall design, and significant added value for the Collaborative Research Centre. At the same time, the programme objective of prioritisation at the applicant universities must be sufficiently honoured.\n\nFunding for cross-border collaborative projects is usually based on the principle of complementarity. It is expected that the foreign partner’s research activities are funded by its host institution and/or a relevant foreign funding agency. Special policies may be in effect based on cooperation agreements between the DFG and foreign partner organisations; this is the case for example for Austria, Israel and China. For research collaborations with developing countries, DFG funding for the foreign partner may be available under certain conditions .','Up to 12 Years, one funding period lasts four years','','research excellence, compelling thematic integration into the overall design, and significant added value for the Collaborative Research Centre\nHigh scientific quality and originality at an internationally competitive level; a complex, long-term research programme; coherent interlinking of projects; researchers with very good track records; appropriate staffing, funding and infrastructure; convincing contributions to development of priority areas and structural development at the applicant universities; support of early career researchers and equality for women and men in research; professional management','No Submission Deadline\nRenewal proposals: must be submitted within the final year of the current funding period of the Collaborative Research Centre;','http://www.dfg.de/en/research_funding/programmes/coordinated_programmes/collaborative_research_centres/in_brief/index.html','http://www.dfg.de/foerderung/programme/koordinierte_programme/sfb/formulare_merkblaetter/index.jsp','','فاند جهت ایجاد مراکز تحقیقاتی دانشگاهی است که پژوهشگران تا حدود 12 سال برروی پروژه های چند رشته ای فعالیت می کنند.\nCollaborative Research Centres  شامل تعداد زیادی پروژه هستند که تعداد و حوزه این پروژه ها بستگی به پروژه تحقیقاتی دارد. هر کدام ازین پروژه ها ممکن است به صورت انفرادی و یا به صورت مشترک توسط چند نفر هدایت شود. \nپژوهشگران غیر آلمانی از کشور های دیگر ممکن است به عنوان نفر اصلی به این پروژه ها (چه در پروژه های انفرادی و یا در شکل محل غیر بومی پروژه ) بپیوندند. \nحمایت مالی پروژه های مشترک بین المللی به صورت مکمل صورت می پذیرد یعنی انتظار می رود فعالیت های پژوهشی افراد غیر آلمانی تحت حمایت مالی موسسه میزبان خارجی و یا موسسات مرتبط قرار گیرد. \n\n','',9),(451,'2017-03-05 11:22:59','2017-03-05 11:22:59','ERC Advanced Grants\n',3,NULL,'If, as an established leading principal investigator, you are interested in the opportunity for long-term funding, the ERC is here to help. ERC Advanced Grants are designed to allow outstanding research leaders of any nationality and any age to pursue ground-breaking, high-risk projects in Europe.\n\nThe scheme targets researchers who have already established themselves as top independent research leaders.  ','up to 5 years','up to € 1.5 million','Eligibility: any nationality, any age. Applicants must be leaders in their respective field(s) of research and must demonstrate significant achievement in the last 10 years\nLocation: research must be conducted in a public or private research organisation (known as a Host Institution/HI). It could be the HI where the applicant already works, or any other HI located in one of the EU Member States or Associated Countries\nFunding: up t','','https://erc.europa.eu/advanced-grants','','','بدون توجه به سن و ملیت و جنیسیت. ینزا است تا در 10 سال گذشته دستاورد قابل توجهی داشته باشد. تا 2/5 میلیون و مدت 5 سال حمات میشود. برنامه باید توسط فرد ارائه شود و تیم خود را مدیریت کند.','',10),(452,'2017-03-05 11:22:59','2017-03-05 11:22:59','ERC Consolidator Grants',3,NULL,'If, as a young principal investigator, you need support to consolidate your independence, the ERC is here to help. ERC Consolidator Grants are designed to back up researchers who want to establish their research teams and continue developing a successful career in Europe. The scheme also strengthens independent and excellent new individual research teams that have been recently created.\n\n','up to 5 years','up to € 2 million','Eligibility: researchers of any nationality with 7-12 years of experience since completion of PhD (extensions are possible – see the latest ERC Work Programme for details), a scientific track record showing scientific talent and an excellent research proposal\nLocation: research must be conducted in a public or private research organisation (known as a Host Institution/HI). It could be the HI where the applicant already works, or any other HI located in one of the EU Member States or Associated Countries','','https://erc.europa.eu/consolidator-grants','','','برنامه ای ویژه پزوهشگران  با 12-7 سال سایقه پژوهش . تا سقف 1/5 میلیون یورو و تا نهایت 5 سال حمایت میشود. برنامه باید توسط فرد ارائه شود و تیم خود را مدیریت کند.','',10),(453,'2017-03-05 11:22:59','2017-03-05 11:22:59','ERC Starting Grants',3,NULL,'If, as a young scientist, you\\\'re interested in making the transition from working under a supervisor to becoming and independent investigator, the ERC is here to help. ERC Starting Grants are designed to encourage young talented research leader to gain independence in Europe and to build their own careers. The scheme targets promising researchers who have the proven potential of becoming independent research leaders.\n\n','up to 5 years','up to € 1.5 million','Eligibility: researchers of any nationality with 2-7 years of experience since completion of PhD (extensions are possible– see the latest ERC Work Programme for details), a scientific track record showing great promise and an excellent research proposal\nLocation: research must be conducted in a public or private research organisation (known as a Host Institution/HI). It could be the HI where the applicant already works, or any other HI located in one of the EU Member States or Associated Countries','','https://erc.europa.eu/funding-and-grants/funding-schemes/starting-grants','','','برنامه ای ویژه پزوهشگران جوان با 2-7 سال سایقه پژوهش که میخواهند مستقل شوند. تا سقف 1/5 میلیون یورو و تا نهایت 5 سال حمایت میشود. برنامه باید توسط فرد ارائه شود و تیم خود را مدیریت کند.','',10),(454,'2017-03-05 11:24:10','2017-03-05 11:28:20','Kick-off Workshops',5,NULL,'Scientific Members of the Max Planck Society are eligible to submit proposals. Proposals are evaluated according to the standard procedures of the Max Planck Society.\nApplications for funds can be made in the following categories:\n- Travel / flight expenses for participants of the workshop\n- Accommodation costs for participants of the workshop\n- Material expenses for printouts, translations, and correspondence\n- Hospitality expenses\n- If required: rental costs / fees for the venue where the event is hosted\nFunding provided through the Max Planck Society should, as a first priority, be used to cover travel expenses and accommodation of the participants from Germany. The host institution is expected to supply matching by providing the necessary local facilities such as conference venue, meals as well as travel expenses and accommodation for participants from the host country. In exceptional cases remaining funds from the allocation made by the Max Planck Society may be used for this purpose. This requires prior approval from the Max Planck Society´s Division for International Relations.\nWithin six weeks after holding the workshop the MPI is required to provide the MPG with a final report with a special focus on the results and outcome as well as a short statement of the expenditures (list of all payments).\nPlease submit applications (by e-mail only) to the Max Planck Society´s Division for International Relations.','','the Max Planck Society provides funding for Kick-Off Workshops up to an amount of € 20,000.','','','','','Contact E-Mail:\nMs. Annette Dvorani, Division for International Relations\ndvorani@gv.mpg.de','اعضا علمی مکس پلانک می توانند پروپوزال ارائه کنند.. تقاضا برای انجام کارگاه ها می بایست توسط مدیر یکی از موسسات مکس پلانک ارائه شود و شامل تاریخ و محل، توضیح موضوع، مزایای برگزاری کارگاه، ساختار و برنامه کارگاه، برآورد هزینه ها باشد.\nتقاضا برای فاند باید در قالب یکی از دسته های : هزینه های سفر برای شرکت کننده ها، هزینه های اقامت شرکت کننده ها، موارد مربوط به ترجمه و مکاتبات، هزینه های میزبانی باشد.\nاولویت اصلی استفاده از فاند مربوط به پوشش هزینه های سفر و اقامت شرکت کننده های آلمانی است. تعیین محل اقامت و غذا به عهده میزبان است. \nشش ماه پس از برگزاری کارگاه موسسه اقدام کننده برای برگزاری باید گزارشی نهایی با تمرکز روی نتایج حاصله از کارگاه و لیست هزینه های صورت گرفته به مکس پلانک ارائه نماید.\nتقاضا برای برگزاری کارگاه می بایست تنها از طریق ایمیل به واحد بین الملل مکس پلانک ارائه شود.\n',' ERROR-NO Tag',11),(455,'2017-03-05 11:24:10','2017-03-05 11:25:52','Individual Doctoral Projects at MPG',1,NULL,'PhD students can complete a doctorate within the scope of research work conducted at a Max Planck Institute.\nApplications can be submitted to the respective institute at any time. Vacancies are advertised on the websites of the individual institutes or the Max Planck job exchange . Job offers and advertisements are also published on Facebook and Twitter.','3 years with possible extension of up to 1 year.','Work contract with a salary based on the collective agreement for public sector employees, currently just under 2,000 euros per month gross. Depending on personal profle and research area, higher remuneration is possible within the frame work of a recruitment allowance. In addition, there is a special annual bonus. An (international) research stay may be subsidised.','PhD students with\n1.an outstanding university degree equivalent to a German Master’s degree 2.an academic qualifcation in an appropriate subject for the advertised PhD researc  or for a relevant PhD research proposal for the respective research project 3.previous research experience 4.a ﬂuent knowledge of the English language','No Submission Deadline','','https://www.mpg.de/jobboard; https://www.mpg.de/institutes','38','دانشجویان مقطع دکترا می توانند دوره دکترای خود را در قالب کار پژوهشی در یکی از موسسات مکس پلاک به پایان برسانند. \nتقاضای داوطلبان می بایست به موسسات مرتبط تقاضای خود را ارائه نمایند.\nپذیرفته شدگان مبلغی حدود 200 یورو به صورت ماهانه دریافت می نمایند.\n\n','undone - research',11),(456,'2017-03-05 11:24:10','2017-03-05 11:26:11','International Max Planck Research Schools',6,NULL,'PhD students can complete a doctorate in a structured programme that provides excellent research conditions. International Max Planck Research Schools (IMPRSs) are jointly managed by Max Planck Institutes and universities. Students have the choice of receiving their doctorates either from the German university or their home university.\nWork contract with a salary based on the collective agreement for public sector employees; doctoral students currently receive just under 2,000 euros per month gross. Depending on personal profle and research area, higher remuneration is possible within the framework of a recruitment allowance. In addition, there is a special annual bonus. An (international) research stay may be subsidised.\nThere is no central application procedure.\nHowever, the International Max Planck Research Schools (IMPRS) – in cooperation with the universities – offer a structured doctoral training program. After completing the usually three-year training period, during which you will be supported both by university supervisors and the Max Planck institute, you will be examined by these two bodies jointly. Since 2009, the figure of Minerva – the logo of the Max Planck Society – has graced many IMPRS doctoral certificates.\nYou will receive a support contract that combines the scientific freedom of a grant with the security of an employment contract  ؟؟؟؟\nIn addition, the Max Planck institutes also offer jobs and grants that are available to any applicant outside of the career path outlined above. If you would like to apply for one of these doctoral positions, you will find the latest calls for applications at our Jobs Exchange. ؟؟؟؟؟','3 years with possible extension by 1 year.','','PhD students with\n1.an outstanding university degree equivalent to a German Master’s degree 2. an academic qualifcation in an appropriate subject for the respective research institute 3.relevant research experience 4. ﬂuent English language skills','Applications must be submitted to the respective IMPRS. Vacancies and application deadlines are advertised on the websites of the respective institutes or research schools','https://www.mpg.de/doctoral_students','https://www.mpg.de/career/how-do-i-get-supported','40','در شهرهای مختلف آلمان و بر اساس رشته های موجود Research Schools وجود دارد که متقاضیان دوره دکترا می توانند خود را در این موسسات با همکاری موسسه مکس پلانک به پایان برسانند.. دانشجو های دوره دکترا می توانند از طریق وبسایت های موسسات برگزار کننده از زمان ثبت نام فرصت های موجود مطلع بشوند. \nدانشجویان دکترا مبلغی حدود 2000 یورو به صورت ماهانه دریافت می کنند. با توجه به حوزه پژوهش کمک هزینه هم می تواند پرداخت شود.امکان پرداخت کمک هزینه اقامت بین المللی نیز وجود دارد.\nیک شیوه ثبت نام واحد برای همه وجود ندارد و شیوه هر موسسه می تواند متفاوت باشد.\nمتقاضی  پس از اتمام دوره سه ساله هم از طریق موسسه و هم از طریق مکس پلانک مورد ارزیابی قرار می گیرد و مهر مکس پلانک نیز در مدرک دکترا لحاظ می شود.\nموضوع پایان نامه نیز با توافق دانشجو و دانشمندان حاضر در موسه انتخاب می گردد.\nشهریه هم برای این دوره در نظر گرفته نشده. متقاضی می بایست دوتوصیه نامه داشته باشه که مستقیم از طریق خود اساتید ارسال ه باشه در صورتی که فرد مستقیما بفرسته ترتیب اثر داده نخواهد شد.','http://www.imprs-quantum.mpg.de/8066/Funding ERROR-NO Tag',11),(457,'2017-03-05 11:24:10','2017-03-05 11:26:27','International Visiting Researchers',6,NULL,'International researchers can conduct independent research at a Max Planck Institute. The programme aims to strengthen cooperation and promote networking between Max Planck Institutes and their international partners.\nGrant and travel allowances are dependent on personal profile and research project.\nApplications must be submitted directly to the respective Max Planck Institute. Vacancies are advertised on the websites of the individual institutes or the Max  As a rule, f\n','Dependent on the host institute. The duration varies and visits can start at any time. PhD students: up to 6 months; postdocs: up to 2 years.','','Scientists with 1. outstanding qualifcations 2.acknowledged research experience','','www.mpg.de/jobboard','','41 ( post doc - PhD students)','پژوهشگران بین المللی میتوانند به صورت مستقل در موسسات مکس پلانک پژوهش انجام دهند. میزان کمک هزینه کاملا براساس موضوع پروژه و همچنین پروفایل شخصی مشخص می گردد.\nتقاضا می بایست مستقیما به موسسه مکس پلانک ارائه شود. \nفرصت ها از طریق وب سایت موسسات مکس پلانک اعلام می گردند.','https://www.mpsd.mpg.de/202156/visiting\n  موسسات مکس پلانک این برنامه ها را پیشتهاد می دهند وتقاضای داوطلب می بایست شامل رزومه، لیست مقالات و نشریات، دو نفر رابط از مکس پلانک، تاییدیه از موسسه مکس پلانک میزبان مبتنی بر حمایت از فعالیت پژوهشی و پروپوزال 2  الی 3 صفحه ای باشد.   ',11),(458,'2017-03-05 11:24:10','2017-03-05 11:26:43','Head of a MPG Research Group',4,NULL,'Junior researchers can conduct independent research work at a Max Planck Institute by establishing their own Max Planck Research Group. Candidates receive their own fxed budget to run their research group, in which PhD students and one postdoc work together on a specifc research topic.\n\n \n\nApplication on advertisement only. Positions at specifc institutes are advertised throughout the year. Central advertisements are normally published once a year in autumn. All positions are advertised in scientifc journals and on their websites as well as on the websites of the respective institutes.\nYou can apply on advertisement only. There are two adverts procedures:\n(1) Advertisements for institute-specific positions and (2) Major advertisements for the centrally announced positions.\nThis program is particularly suitable for excellent young applicants who have already held one or two post-doc jobs and who would now like to – and deem themselves apt to – head a group and to elaborate together on own research ideas independently. Please note that MPRG-L positions are only open to applicants who hold a doctorate.\n\n','5 years with two possible extensions of up to 2 years each.','The level of funding depends on the respective research area and research focus. It covers funding for staﬀ, materials and operating costs, including the researcher’s own salary (based on the remuneration system for university teachers, current minimum 5,400 euros per month gross).','Highly qualifed postdocs who 1. have viable and innovative ideas 2. have ideally already had one to two postdoctoral positions 3.are in a position to realise an independent research project','','https://www.mpg.de/mprg/faqs','https://www.mpg.de/career/max-planck-research-groups','29','پژوهشگران می توانند به صورت مستقل کار پژوهشی خود را در یکی از موسسات مکس پلانک با ایجاد گروه های پژوهشی خود انجام دهند. متقاضیان به منظور ایجاد  گروه های خود بودجه ثابتی را دریافت می کنند.\nاین گروه ها شامل دانشجویان دکترا و پسا دکتری با موضوع پژوهشی مشخص می باشند.\nمیزان بودجه بر اساس حوزه تحقیقاتی مشخص می گردد و شامل فاند برای پرسنل مواد و حقوق خود محقق می شود.( در حدود 5400 یورو در ماه)\nزمان پذیرش در طول سال از طریق موسسات اعلام می گردد.\nفرد متقاضی می بایست در زمان تقاضا یک یا دو پست پسا دکترا داشته باشد.\nمتقاضی تنها از طریق تبلیغات اعلام شده می تواند برای سرپرستی گروه های پژوهشی اقدام نماید. اولین گزینه فرصت های ارائه شده توسط موسسه متبوع که معمولا در ژورنال های علمی  و وبسایت موسسات مکس پلانک اعلام می شوند و گزینه دوم موقعیت های اعلام شده از موسسه مرکزی مکس پلانک می باشد که که معمولا یک بار در پاییز بدون محدویت موضوعی اعلام می شوند.\nاین فرصت معمولا برای محققان جوان مناسب می باشد که علاقمند به تشکیل گروه های پژوهشی مستقل می باشند و فقط برای دارنگان مدرک دکترا قابل استفاده می باشد.','',11),(459,'2017-03-05 11:24:10','2017-03-05 11:27:06','Grants for Advanced Postdoctoral Training',4,NULL,'Junior researchers can gain additional knowledge and skills at a Max Planck Institute on the basis of their prior professional qualifcations – for example, as a project leader at a Max Planck Institute.\nWork contract with a salary based on the collective agreement for public sector employees. The salary is agreed depending on personal profle and research project.\nPositions are advertised in scientifc journals (also in international publications), on the Max Planck job exchange or on the website of the respective institute. It is also possible to take the initiative and contact the respective MPI directly.','As a rule, work contracts are limited to 2 to 3 years.','','Postdocs with 1. an outstanding doctorate in a relevant feld completed up to 10 years ago 2. at least 2 years of research experience','','www.mpg.de/jobboard','','45','پژوهشگران می توانند به عنوان سرپرست پروژه در یکی از موسسات مرتبط مکس پلانک بر اساس position های پیشنهاد شده در سایت های موسسات مکس پلانک اقدام نمایند.','داخل سایت مکس پلانک توضیح و فاند خاصی تحت این عنوان و یا عناوین مشابه وجود ندارد. مگر مورد مشابه در 217 که به عنوان سرپرست گروه علمی فعالیت نمایند.',11);
